com.ti.debug.engine.scripting

Class Options

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ti.debug.engine.scripting.Options

  • public class Options
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates the debug properties methods. An instance of this class is automatically created when a new session is opened.

    // Create Environment and open a debug session
    ScriptingEnvironment env = new ScriptingEnvironment();
    DebugServer myServer = (DebugServer) env.getServer("DebugServer.1");
    DebugSession mySession = myServer.openSession("*", "*");

    ...

    // Get value of property
    bool value = mySession.options.getBoolean(id);

    ...

    // set value of property
    mySession.options.setBoolean(id,value);

    ...

    // get list of properties, based on regular expression
    mySession.options.printOptions(regex);

        Searches for and returns the value of the Boolean option with the given id. A ScriptingException is thrown if an option with the id is not found, or if it is found but is not of type Boolean.

      • loadSessionSettings

        public void loadSessionSettings(java.lang.String filePath)
                         throws ScriptingException
        Load the values of the options from a given session file. These files can be generated from CCS UniFlash GUI application and loaded in your script so that the settings will be the same in both instances. For multi-core devices, one session file can be used to load settings for each core. Note that the CPU name has to match in your Target Configuration file for the loading to be successful.
        Parameters:
        filePath - String the full path to the session file
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • optionExist

        public boolean optionExist(java.lang.String id)
        Determine if the given ID maps to a valid option in the current session
        Parameters:
        id - String identifying the option
        Returns:
        true if there is an associated option to the given ID, false otherwise

      • printOptionById

        public void printOptionById(java.lang.String id)
                     throws ScriptingException
        Prints information on an option based on the ID, or if it is a node/group, print information on all options that are children properties of the property matching the ID. Information printed includes option id, name, value, default value, type, and for type ChoiceList, valid choices.
        Parameters:
        id - String identifying the option
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • printOptions

        public void printOptions(java.lang.String regex)
                  throws ScriptingException
        Prints information on all options which match the given regular expression. A search is performed for options with IDs or names. Information printed includes option id, name, value, default value, type, and for type ChoiceList, valid choices.
        Parameters:
        regex - the regular expression to which options are to be matched
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • setBoolean

        public void setBoolean(java.lang.String id,
                       boolean value)
                throws ScriptingException
        Searches for the Boolean option with the given id, and sets it to the given value. A ScriptingException is thrown if: 1. An option with the id is not found OR 2. if it is found but is not of type Boolean OR 3. if it is disabled or read only (ie; cannot be set)
        Parameters:
        id - String identifying the option
        value - boolean value to which to set the option
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • setString

        public void setString(java.lang.String id,
                      java.lang.String value)
               throws ScriptingException
        Searches for the String option with the given id, and sets it to the given value. Type String may not contain newlines. A ScriptingException is thrown if: 1. An option with the id is not found OR 2. if it is found but is not of type String, StringList, or ChoiceList OR 3. if the option is of type StringList or ChoiceList and the given value is not a valid choice OR 4. if it is disabled or read only (ie; cannot be set)
        Parameters:
        id - String identifying the option
        value - String value to which to set the option
        Throws:
        ScriptingException
